video.title: COMEDIANS of the world
video.synopsis: A diverse set of 47 comedians from 13 regions bring their perspective on what's funny around the world. Browse and discover by selecting "Episodes."

episodes.synopsis: Accidental combovers. Arachnophobia. Amsterdam mushrooms. And terrifying family ski trips. Martijn Koning bares his many flaws, fears and foibles.
episodes.title: Martijn Koning

episodes.synopsis: Filter? Soundos el Ahmadi doesn't need a filter. She candidly reveals the price she's paid for looking good, having a baby and bottling up her anger.
episodes.title: Soundos el Ahmadi

episodes.synopsis: Rayen Panday enumerates the difficulties of being single in his 30s, the one job he could never do and the two types of people in the world.
episodes.title: Rayen Panday

episodes.synopsis: Quebecois comedian Louis-José Houde riffs on the enigma of the dark web, the fearlessness of Montréalers and Mozart as the original rock star.
episodes.title: Louis-José Houde

episodes.synopsis: François Bellefeuille's lively set takes on the challenges of vomiting kids, electric cars and a supremely awkward encounter with a horse.
episodes.title: François Bellefeuille

episodes.synopsis: Katherine Levac digs deep and divulges droll tales of chasing her first crush, hanging with hockey players and crashing a medical school class.
episodes.title: Katherine Levac

episodes.synopsis: Unmasking the contradictions in human nature, Adib Alkhalidey recounts the reality of being vegetarian, Christopher Columbus's little secret and more.
episodes.title: Adib Alkhalidey

episodes.synopsis: With irreverent impersonations and stories that get personal, Ibraheem Alkhairallah reveals secrets to advertising, marital bliss and social media.
episodes.title: Ibraheem Alkhairallah

episodes.synopsis: In a rapid-fire set, Rawsan Hallak sounds off on the perils of physical fitness, the pressure to get married and long-distance calls to her mom.
episodes.title: Rawsan Hallak

episodes.synopsis: The self-proclaimed "shortest comedian in the Middle East" shares revelations from his eclectic family and an awkward brush with a celebrity.
episodes.title: Adi Khalefa

episodes.synopsis: It's all fun and games until someone ends up behind bars. Moayad Alnefaie tells stories of childhood mischief that went way too far.
episodes.title: Moayad Alnefaie

episodes.synopsis: Shirley Souagnon playfully details an awkward gig in Haiti, the challenges of giving up her iPhone and her newfound empathy for straight women.
episodes.title: Shirley Souagnon

episodes.synopsis: Jamel Comedy Club alum Jason Brokerss blends the personal and the political as he talks airport profiling, life goals and growing up poor.
episodes.title: Jason Brokerss

episodes.synopsis: From pink pens to waxing mishaps to underwhelming sex: Tania Dutel breaks down life's indignities in a show that gets more revealing by the minute.
episodes.title: Tania Dutel

episodes.synopsis: Donel Jack'sman counts down the four comic bits his mother hates most as he riffs on horror movies, absurd stereotypes, relationships and more.
episodes.title: Donel Jack'sman

episodes.synopsis: Thiago Ventura dishes on the humble beginnings of his career, the weird ways in which preppies respond to him and the perks of walking with a cane.
episodes.title: Thiago Ventura

episodes.synopsis: Mhel Marrer gives her unique take on everything from sexism to social media, and also compares ride-hailing services to the world's oldest profession.
episodes.title: Mhel Marrer

episodes.synopsis: Afonso Padilha dissects the myriad of items people purchase at the pharmacy and doles out some helpful hints on how to navigate being kind of a wimp.
episodes.title: Afonso Padilha

episodes.synopsis: Feeling the pressure of representing German comedy, Enissa Amani discusses her imprisoned fans, subtitle goofs and the fallacy of "couple goals."
episodes.title: Enissa Amani

episodes.synopsis: Leaving the pink tracksuit behind, Ilka Bessin gets real with a personal set about her boyfriend, excessive sweating, dirty nursery rhymes and more.
episodes.title: Ilka Bessin

episodes.synopsis: Learning German is tough, but Kaya Yanar nails a few regional dialects and comments on driving in Switzerland, funny German laws and Dutch bad guys.
episodes.title: Kaya Yanar

episodes.synopsis: Franco Escamilla recounts the fertility woes and sexual struggles endured by his dog, Hunter. Luckily, this puppy tale has multiple happy endings.
episodes.title: Franco Escamilla

episodes.synopsis: After beating cancer, Hugo "El Cojo Feliz" will laugh about anything, including cool ways to die, Tinder for socks and a wild border control idea.
episodes.title: Hugo El Cojo Feliz

episodes.synopsis: Adulthood has snuck up on Gaby Llanas and she is not pleased. She is, however, enjoying her emotional bond with tupperware.
episodes.title: Gaby Llanas

episodes.synopsis: CEO-turned-comic Atul Khatri spills knowledge on 25 years of marriage, airport immigration and navigating boys' trips as a 50-year-old man.
episodes.title: Atul Khatri

episodes.synopsis: Aditi Mittal lays down the truth about Turkish coffee, dude culture in the workplace and people who still think females can't be funny.
episodes.title: Aditi Mittal

episodes.synopsis: From the politics of children's birthday parties to the drama of dining out, family man Amit Tandon has some thoughts on being the average Indian dad.
episodes.title: Amit Tandon

episodes.synopsis: Doctor-turned-comedian Riaad Moosa riffs on regional dialects, personal hygiene disasters and the unfailing awkwardness of airline travel.
episodes.title: Riaad Moosa

episodes.synopsis: In her first North American performance, Tumi Morake unpacks life's greatest mysteries, including fast food, rap music and the physics of fertility.
episodes.title: Tumi Morake

episodes.synopsis: In an open address to "foodies" everywhere, Loyiso Gola critiques white privilege and problematic pop culture, one hilarious anecdote at a time.
episodes.title: Loyiso Gola

episodes.synopsis: When does dance music go too far? Loyiso Madinga has the answer -- and other candid theories on race, religion and the worst part of "Black Panther."
episodes.title: Loyiso Madinga

episodes.synopsis: Urzila Carlson celebrates all that New Zealand has to offer: hot accents, intimidating baristas and straight couples who are terrible at arguing.
episodes.title: Urzila Carlson

episodes.synopsis: Hailing from the shark attack capital of the world, Joel Creasey brags about dating an underwear model and recounts his worst driving fails.
episodes.title: Joel Creasey

episodes.synopsis: As the son of Sri Lankan immigrants, Nazeem Hussain knows he stands out in Australia. But he's found a fun way to fight racism: prank phone calls.
episodes.title: Nazeem Hussain

episodes.synopsis: Colorful comic Cal Wilson opens up about her weirdest fears, her most mortifying moments and the perils of sexting in the autocorrect era.
episodes.title: Cal Wilson

episodes.synopsis: Joel Dommett helpfully demonstrates why Venetian blinds can't be closed angrily, how to climb a sleeping airplane seatmate and one use for nunchucks.
episodes.title: Joel Dommett

episodes.synopsis: Controlled by a "psychopathic French-Canadian brain shrimp," Mae Martin recalls obsessions with drugs and superstar performer Bette Midler.
episodes.title: Mae Martin

episodes.synopsis: The "unbearably delightful" Nish Kumar examines the right-wing qualities of a classic board game and the disadvantages of solo concert attendance.
episodes.title: Nish Kumar

episodes.synopsis: A pregnant Ellie Taylor reveals the challenges of child-bearing, including having one's bits fiddled with and sudden-onset candle appreciation.
episodes.title: Ellie Taylor

episodes.synopsis: DeAnne Smith opens up about her hatred of escape rooms, shampoo homophobia and how she and her dog are a conservative Republican's nightmare.
episodes.title: DeAnne Smith

episodes.synopsis: Say hello to Ivan Decker. He's here to share his thoughts on zombie teeth, weaponized lobsters and the sinister lie behind instant noodles.
episodes.title: Ivan Decker

episodes.synopsis: Buckle up for Dave Merheje's frenetic stories about growing up as the child of Lebanese immigrants who, well, probably should have gotten a divorce.
episodes.title: Dave Merheje

episodes.synopsis: K. Trevor Wilson delivers a deadpan dissertation on "pet parents," the perils of one-ply toilet paper and his sometimes misplaced faith in flatulence.
episodes.title: K. Trevor Wilson

episodes.synopsis: It's been a rough year for humans. But Neal Brennan's here with thoughtfully hilarious musings on a trip to Germany, dating in the #MeToo era and more.
episodes.title: Neal Brennan

episodes.synopsis: Chris D'Elia was bewildered by a trip Down Under. He also hates know-it-alls and thinks TED Talks are for dummies. But he loves being a comedian.
episodes.title: Chris D'Elia

episodes.synopsis: Bawdy comic Nicole Byer tells a lot of fat jokes -- so get over it. And there's no need to tell her she's beautiful. She already knows.
episodes.title: Nicole Byer

episodes.synopsis: Nick Swardson's in his 40s and forgot to have kids. But he's got a hot tip based on personal experience: Never, ever fart on a plane.
episodes.title: Nick Swardson
